<HEAD>Jesse Jackson Raps President on Civil Rights</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Rev. Jesse Jackson says President Bush has
offered no substance to support his professed commitment to civil
rights.
   Jackson, interviewed on NBC-TV's ``Meet the Press'' on Sunday,
criticized Bush for backing recent Supreme Court rulings opposed by
civil rights leaders, failing to strengthen the Civil Rights
Commission and lacking a comprehensive plan to fight drugs.
   He credited Bush for directing less antagonism toward civil
rights than did his predecessor Ronald Reagan, but added: ``So far,
no substance.''
