<HEAD>Rain Widespread After Storms Hit Plains, Rockies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain dampened much of the Eastern Seaboard, Gulf Coast and
Plains early today after severe thunderstorms hit parts of the
Plains and Rockies.
   Thunderstorms on Sunday produced wind gusts near 60 mph at
Abilene, Kan., and Great Falls, Mont., and gusts of about 80 mph
were recorded at Lewiston, Mont. Winds caused some damage in parts
of South Carolina.
   Flooding of small streams was widespread in northeast Colorado
and several roads were washed out, including Highway 6 near Paoli.
   Heavy rain also caused flooding of a highway between Almena and
