<FIRST>u i PM-NIreland-Bomb     07-31 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-NIreland-Bomb,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Large IRA Bomb Explodes Downtown After Hundreds Evacuated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A large IRA bomb loaded in a
laundry van exploded downtown in front of a heavily guarded court
building after hundreds of people were evacuated from the area,
police said.
   Three people were treated for shock after the blast outside the
Northern Ireland Court building, which caused widespread damage to
buildings in the area and wrecked 14 cars, police said.
   The bombers evaded tight security around the court to park a
laundry van in which they hid a bomb estimated to weigh 1,000
pounds, said a police spokesman.
   The spokesman, who refused to be named, said hundreds of office
workers and shoppers were evacuated from the area when a warning
call was received 35 minutes before the blast.
   Northern Ireland's law and order minister Peter Cope said the
courthouse will be closed for two days because of the
``considerable damage.''
   ``I am glad nobody was hurt or injured,'' he added.
   The outlawed Irish Republican Army later claimed it planted the
bomb. The IRA is fighting to oust the British from the province and
unite it with the Republic of Ireland.
</TEXT>
