Grande Cafe on Sunday night.
   Barbara Bush was at Kennebunkport, Maine, at their oceanfront
home. The commerce secretary also came without his wife, Georgette.
   Bush skipped another event originally planned for the evening,
the finals of the Sovran Tennis Classic at an outdoor Washington
arena. It rained intermittently during the afternoon and evening.
   Bush, clad in a sports shirt and yellow blazer, ignored
questions from reporters as he left the restaurant.
