<FIRST>r a AM-DejaVuBirth     07-31 0248</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Deja Vu Birth,0255</SECOND>
<HEAD>Couple Gives Birth in Blue Subaru _ Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MERRIMACK, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Maybe it's the color or the make, but two
of Athena and Tom Chisholm's three children have been born in blue
Subarus.
   Sunday morning Mrs. Chisholm told her husband it was time to go
to the hospital in Manchester.
   But the drive from Merrimack was interrupted two miles from home
with an urgent stop by the road in Bedford and the arrival of a
7-pound, 10-ounce daughter in the front seat of their blue 1987
Subaru.
   ``The baby was sliding out. All I could do was catch her,''
Chisholm said.
   It was deja vu for the couple, who 2{ years ago delivered a son
in the back of their old blue Subaru.
   ``It's a lot easier to take the second time around,'' Chisholm
said.
   ``It was just very easy,'' his wife said. ``I wish everyone
could have kids that easy, but I was still surprised that it went
that quick.''
   Their daughter, yet to be named, has two older brothers,
Christopher, 6, and Paul, the first Subaru arrival.
   When Paul was born, it was 30 degrees and the wind was blowing.
``This birth was more pleasant than the last time,'' Chisholm said.
   Mrs. Chisholm, 30, is studying for her master's degree in early
childhood development at the University of New Hampshire and
teaches part-time at Hesser College. Her husband, 33, has been laid
off from his job with a Massachusetts firm.
</TEXT>
