<FIRST>r i AM-France-Fires     07-31 0164</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-France-Fires,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>Forest Fires Rage On Riviera, Corsica; Two Tourists Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Forest and brush fires raged along the French
Riviera and on the Mediterranean island of Corsica Monday, killing
two Italian tourists who drove into a wall of fire, police reported.
   The tourists, who were not immediately identified, were driving
near Corsica's northern tip when their auto ran into the flames
that destroyed more than 2,500 acres of scrub land, according to
police. They said two other people in the car suffered serious
injuries and burns.
   Several campgrounds were ordered evacuated and members of the
French Foreign Legion posted on the island were helping fight the
fires.
   Fires have broken out all along the Riviera, which is suffering
searing temperatures and gusty winds. Most were put out quickly.
   Threatening flames moved up to the outskirts of Nice's suburbs.
Police said many people rushed home from work to make sure their
houses were safe, but only one building was ordered evacuated.
</TEXT>
