<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Norway's unemployment rate stood at 3.9
percent in July, unchanged from the previous month but up from 2.1
percent a year earlier, the government reported Monday.
   The number of jobless rose by 300 to 85,600 from the end of
June. The unemployment figure a year ago was 45,300.
   Norway's jobless rate reached a post-war record at the end of
January of 4.0 percent, with 86,000 people registered as out of
work.
