<HEAD>Omaha Company Purchases Stock In France Seafood Distributor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ConAgra Inc. Monday announced the purchase of
50 percent of Gelazur, S.A., a leading European seafood distributor.
   Gelazur, based in Nice, France, has annual sales of about $60
million. No purchase price was disclosed.
   ConAgra, based in Omaha, is a diversified food company with
annual sales exceeding $11 billion.
   T. Truxtun Morrison, president and chief operating officer of
ConAgra International, said Roger Kourcia will continue as chairman
of Gelazur, which will be part of London-based ConAgra Europe.
ConAgra Europe will relocate its headquarters to Brussels, Belgium,
Aug. 1.
   ConAgra operates basic food companies in Spain and Portugal, 11
trading offices in several European countries and is a
joint-venture partner with W. Jordan Millers Ltd. operating an
oat-processing mill in England.
