<FIRST>u f AM-Manischewitz     07-31 0308</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Manischewitz,0321</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kosher Food Maker Breaks Off Merger Agreement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   B. Manischewitz Co., a leading maker of
kosher foods, said Monday it has terminated a merger agreement with
a Los Angeles investment firm, blaming what it called the firm's
unwillingness to complete the deal.
   Under the merger agreement, the 100-year-old company, best known
for the kosher wine that bears its name, was to be acquired by
Levine, Tessler, Leichtman &amp; Co. at $841 per share.
   ``It has become clear from the words and conduct of LTL that LTL
is not prepared or willing to close the merger,'' Manischewitz said
in a news release. The disagreement stems from a federal grand jury
investigation of alleged violations of the antitrust laws in the
kosher food industry.
   The investment firm claims Manischewitz refused to provide
information on the investigation, and that the refusal violated the
merger agreement. The company disagreed.
   Both sides, in news releases, expressed a willingness to
complete the deal.
   ``LTL regrets the company's decision not to provide the
necessary information,'' said Arthur E. Levine in a release issued
by his firm. ``In view of the decision, however, LTL intends to
enforce its rights under the merger agreement, including its right
to receive certain payments upon termination of the agreement.''
   A secretary at Levine, Tessler and Leichtman who would not give
her name said she could not confirm the amount sought in break-up
fees.
   Manischewitz officials said they were told of a $2.4 million fee.
   Both sides said they wish to avoid litigation over the issue and
have agreed to a two-day period in which neither party would file a
lawsuit against the other.
   Manischewitz has also received conditional offers from National
Foods Inc., of New York, and from Berisford Capital Corp., acting
with Santa Monica Partners, J. Morton Davis and other individual
investors.
</TEXT>
