<FILEID>AP-NR-07-31-89 2143EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Abbott-Lilly     07-31 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Abbott-Lilly,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Abbott, Lilly Settle Litigation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Abbott Laboratories on Monday announced the
settlement of all litigation involving an Eli Lilly &amp; Co.
subsidiary that had accused the North Chicago pharmaceutical
company of patent infringement.
   The settlement ends four separate legal actions pending in U.S.
District Court in Los Angeles. Terms of the settlement with the
Lilly subsidiary, Hybritech Inc. of San Diego, were not disclosed.
   One of the cases involved Hybritech's 1986 claim that pregnancy
tests and other diagnostic tests marketed by Abbott unlawfully used
technology developed by Hybritech.
   The other matters settled by the agreement are an antitrust case
against Abbott, which was on appeal following a jury verdict in
Abbott's favor; an Abbott lawsuit charging Hybritech with
misappropriating marketing and research secrets through former
Abbott workers now employed by Hybritech; and a Hybritech lawsuit
alleging Abbott infringed on a patent covering a method and
apparatus for analyzing immune systems.
   Abbott is a diversified health care company and a leader in
diagnostic equipment. Hybritech, which manufactures and sells
diagnostic equipment, was acquired by Indianpolis-based Lilly in
1984.
</TEXT>
